ADI FILMS, LLC IS A SINGLE MEMBER LLC, WHOLLY OWNED BY ANIMAL DEFENDERS INTERNATIONAL, INC. THE TWO COMPANIES SHARE A FACILITY AND EMPLOYEES. ADI FILMS, LLC IS CONSOLIDATED WITH THE ORGANIZATION FOR TAX AND FINANCIAL PURPOSES.

The Nobel Foundation Rights Association (NFRA) is a Swedish nonprofit organization established in 1999 to provide informational, research, museum, media and related activities within the Nobel Foundation's "sphere of interest". Its sole "permanent member" is the Nobel Foundation. NFRA does not currently have any or anticipate having any U.S. tax obligations; therefore, it has neither applied for an EIN or for recognition of its exempt status. It appears, however, that NFRA would qualify as a foreign equivalent of a U.S. public charity as a Type I supporting organization. The Nobel Peace Center Foundation (Stiftelsen Nobels Fredssenter) is a Norwegian Foundation that presents the Nobel Peace Prize Laureates through exhibitions, seminars, and conferences. The Alfred Nobel Memorial Foundation (ANMF) is a Swedish nonprofit organization. ANMF does not currently have any or anticipate having any U.S. tax obligations; therefore, it has neither applied for an EIN or for recognition of its exempt status. It appears, however, that ALMF would qualify as a foreign equivalent of a U.S. public charity.

Nobel Group Interests AB ("NGI") was formed in the latter part of 2012 to facilitate financial and administrative coordination between the companies and is a fully owned subsidiary of NFRA. NGI in its turn is the owner of Nobel Media AB, Nobel Museum AB, Nobelhuset AB, and Nobel Peace Prize-Research and Info AS (former Nobel Peace Prize Concert AS). All the companies are for-profit subsidiaries under NFRA and, similar to NFRA, currently have no U.S. tax reporting obligation. Therefore, no company has an EIN. Furthermore, because they are "C Corporations" by virtue of the business entity classification in Treasury Regulation Section 301.7701-2(b)(a) the formula provided in the instruction to Schedule R for calculation of "share of total income and "share of the end-of-year assets" is inapplicable.
